cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC

This paper deals with automatic photo cropping, which is a task related to computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses learning-to-rank algorithms, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG). Hence, cs.IR and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper presents a new dataset, which involves human annotations, and evaluates the performance of various algorithms. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (MM) and human-computer interaction (HC) sub-categories.
